laura stokes center for medieval and early modern studies skip to main content home login center for medieval and early modern studies enter your keywords main menu about programs courses people blogs news calendar resources you are here home laura stokes assistant professor email lpstokes stanford edu website http www stanford edu dept history people stokes_laura html courses there aren t any courses listed for this professor yet laura stokes completed her ph d at the university of virginia in 2006 her dissertation demons of urban reform examines the origins of witchcraft prosecution in fifteenth century europe against the backdrop of a general rise in the prosecution of crime and other measures of social control in the process she has investigated the relationship between witchcraft and sodomy persecutions as well as the interplay between the unregulated development of judicial torture and innovations within witchcraft prosecution she is currently in the process of revising the dissertation into a book manuscript her future research plans include a social history of greed in the age of the reformation selected publications demons of urban reform the rise of witchcraft prosecution 1430 1530 palgrave macmillan 2011 translator of johannes dillinger bose leute a comparative study of witch hunts in swabian austria and the electorate of trier university of virginia press forthcoming translator of sonke lorenz germany southwestern in richard golden ed encyclopedia of witchcraft the western tradition santa barbara abc clio 2006 nurnberg and luzern in the hexenforschung lexikon at www historicum net center for medieval and early modern studies pigott hall building 260 450 serra mall stanford ca 94350 director cecile alduy alduy stanford edu web manager biliana kassabova bilianak stanford edu follow cmemsstanford facebook contact map & directions
